1.name: Squat
1.notes: The top single here should be at or just below your planned opener. Play it smart based on fatigue levels and realize the goal of this week is to essentially maintain the adaptation from all of the previous work, as well as allow for the fatigue we've got built up to dissipate.

1.name: Bench
1.notes: Again, top single should be at or around opener.

1.name: Deadlift
1.notes: Top single here should be at or around last warmup. If you feel like you need it, you can do a speed and technique here. It's going to carry over beyond just your recovery, but I also think specifically with the deadlift we can usually allow a bit of extra recovery.

3.name: Rest Day
3.notes:
See the notes below
If you're competing on Saturday, I'd recommend the following weekly structure for taper week: Monday - off - Weds - off - off - Competition. You can feel free to adjust around your schedule as well - it's probably better to get the lifts in when you have the time and energy to be present and put focus into the sessions as opposed to cramming it into a busy day to line up with an "ideal" schedule.

4.name: Competition Day
4.notes: If you haven't already, ensure you join the Discord using the "community" tab and clicking on the CBB logo. Danil and/or myself can help with attempt selection, reviewing openers the week of, and taper modifications as well. Also, there is a mock competition free download in the Discord that can help you with planning attempts for competition day, so make sure to check that out.
